Name: uterine corpus endometrial carcinoma
Definition: A uterine corpus cancer that is derives_from the inner lining of the uterus.

Name: uterine body mixed cancer
Definition: A uterine corpus cancer that has_material_basis_in more than one type of cell.
Synonym: malignant mixed tumor of Corpus Uteri

Name: adenomyoma of uterine corpus
Definition: A uterine corpus cancer that has_material_basis_in gland and muscle components.

Name: uterine corpus sarcoma
Definition: An uterine corpus cancer that is located_in the muscles of the uterus or located_in other tissues that support the uterus.

Name: uterine corpus serous adenocarcinoma
Definition: A uterine corpus cancer that is characterized histologically by papillae with fibrovascular cores

Name: uterus perivascular epithelioid cell tumor
Definition: A perivascular epithelioid cell tumor that is located_in the uterus.

Name: uterine corpus choriocarcinoma
Definition: A choriocarcinoma that is located_in the uterine corpus.
Synonym: Gestational Choriocarcinoma of the fallopian tube

Name: mixed endometrial stromal and smooth muscle tumor
Definition: A uterine corpus cancer that has_material_basis_in endometrial stroma and smooth muscle cells.

Name: isthmus cancer
Definition: A lysosomal storage disease that involves the accumulation of harmful amounts of lipids (fats) in some of the body's cells and tissues.
